  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Myroga",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png",
            "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Myroga Hoards",
          "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
          "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
                "aonid": 290,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover)",
              "page": 266,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Like most dragons, myrogas often amass sizable hoards of treasure in the course of their long, violent lives. A myroga\u2019s treasures tend to be eccentric and strange. Powerful crystal balls, cursed suits of armor, and intelligent talking weapons are among the most commonplace treasures found in a myroga\u2019s hoard of wonders.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "link": {
            "alt": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
            "aonid": 290,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover)",
          "page": 266,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Myrogas are avaricious, simple-minded dragons with supernatural occult powers. They draw their amazing abilities from ley lines\u2014loci of intense magical energy often associated with psychic phenomena.  \n  \nA myroga encountered away from a ley line is far less dangerous, a fact which myrogas recognize and take great pains to mitigate. Upon discovering an unoccupied ley line, a myroga is apt to roost nearby and guard the site ferociously. All the while, they sup on the ley line's nearly inexhaustible ambient magic to grow stronger and expand their repertoire of brutal powers.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
      "link": {
        "alt": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
        "aonid": 290,
        "game-obj": "Sources",
        "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover) pg. 266",
        "type": "link"
      },
      "name": "Gatewalkers (Hardcover)",
      "page": 266,
      "type": "source"
    }
  ],
